{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-06-11-1",
 "title": "Small Talk at the Spaceport",
 "summary": "At the Coronet spaceport, the businesswoman Shannon arrives by shuttle eager to catch her husband's race and pauses to admire a swoop being unloaded from the Triton by the disguised agent Bazil McKenzie (in his scarred, green-haired Mege Vauki guise). The two strike up friendly small talk about the swoop, which Bazil is still paying off through his winnings, and Shannon encourages him after learning it was his first tournament. Bazil explains that first place in his Grade One division would win a ship and twenty-five thousand credits, though he has settled into third after a strong rookie run. They exchange good wishes and names before Bazil dons his helmet, revs the swoop, and rides off into the spaceport traffic.",
